    "The reasonably paid journalists and television producers of the mass media have been displaced by the unpaid creative work of users in social media (Kalantzis-Cope 2016).",
    "On the backs of unpaid laborers, the new media barons have made themselves fabulously rich.",
    "More agency may have been granted to users than in the older mass media allowed, but this has come at a price.AI changes the game again.",
    "Social media is increasingly driven more by interest algorithms, and less by user navigation.",
    "Google was the first to build user profiles from search and by scraping user-created documents and emails (Zuboff 2019)."
